noun: the round fruit of a tree of the rose family.noun: a structure carrying a road or path across a river or gap.noun: a visible mass of condensed water vapour floating in the atmosphere.noun: the first appearance of light in the sky before sunrise.noun: a sound caused by reflection of sound waves from a surface.noun: a hot glowing body of burning gas produced by combustion.noun: an open space in a forest.noun: a fierce or angry stare.noun: a vitreous substance fused onto the surface of pottery.noun: elegance and beauty of movement or expression.noun: a particular level of rank, quality, or value.noun: a berry growing in clusters on a vine, used for wine.noun: a place of burial for a dead body.verb: to feed on growing grass or other plants.noun: a small wood or group of trees.noun: the process or period of gathering crops from fields.noun: a hard creamy-white material from the tusks of an elephant.noun: an area of land overgrown with dense tropical vegetation.noun: a metal container with a lid and spout used for boiling water.noun: a lamp with a transparent case protecting the flame from the wind.noun: a field of grass, especially one used for hay or grazing.adjective: of small width in proportion to length or height.noun: a very large expanse of sea covering most of the earth's surface.noun: a person who journeys to a sacred place for religious reasons.noun: a place from which stone or other materials are extracted.noun: a question or statement phrased so as to require ingenuity to answer.noun: a dark area or shape produced by an object blocking light.noun: wood prepared for use in building and carpentry.noun: a natural pigment of a dark yellowish-brown colour.noun: a low area of land between hills or mountains.noun: a tree or shrub with narrow leaves, typically growing near water.noun: a heavy inert gaseous element occurring in trace amounts in air.verb: to have an intense longing or desire for something.noun: the time at which something is most powerful or successful.